abstract: Iran’s leaders disqualified more than 7,000 candidates, including most moderates and centrists, paving the way for tougher domestic and foreign policies.
snippet: Iran’s leaders disqualified more than 7,000 candidates, including most moderates and centrists, paving the way for tougher domestic and foreign policies.
lead_paragraph: When Iranians go to the polls on Friday they will be taking part in what may be the least representative and least fair election in the Islamic Republic’s history.

abstract: Five hungry candidates with sticks and one ex-mayor taking the hits. Bernie Sanders should be grateful.
snippet: Five hungry candidates with sticks and one ex-mayor taking the hits. Bernie Sanders should be grateful.

abstract: Democrats already see reality through the Bernie lens.
snippet: Democrats already see reality through the Bernie lens.
lead_paragraph: Successful presidential candidates are mythmakers. They don’t just tell a story. They tell a story that helps people make meaning out of the current moment; that divides people into heroes and villains; that names a central challenge and explains why they are the perfect person to meet it.

abstract: Democratic presidential hopeful Elizabeth Warren on Thursday declined to disavow a new super PAC that has earmarked $1 million to back her candidacy, an apparent reversal from her vigorous opposition to the outside spending groups that have become central to American politics.
snippet: Democratic presidential hopeful Elizabeth Warren on Thursday declined to disavow a new super PAC that has earmarked $1 million to back her candidacy, an apparent reversal from her vigorous opposition to the outside spending groups that have become...
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Democratic presidential hopeful Elizabeth Warren on Thursday declined to disavow a new super PAC that has earmarked $1 million to back her candidacy, an apparent reversal from her vigorous opposition to the outside spending groups that have become central to American politics.
headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Appears to Drop Opposition to Unlimited-Money Group Backing Her Campaign

abstract: Intelligence officials have warned lawmakers that Russia is interfering in the 2020 election campaign to help President Donald Trump get reelected, according to three officials familiar with the closed-door briefing.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Intelligence officials have warned lawmakers that Russia is interfering in the 2020 election campaign to help President Donald Trump get reelected, according to three officials familiar with the closed-door briefing.
headline_main: Intel Officials Say Russia Boosting Trump Candidacy
